Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "prljave" in different forms and positions:

1. *Prljave* ruke nemoj da stavljaš na belu košulju. (Don't put your *dirty* hands on the white shirt.)
2. *Prljave* čarape nisu za nošenje na venčanju. (*Dirty* socks are not for wearing at a wedding.)
3. Moramo očistiti *prljave* sudove pre večere. (We need to clean the *dirty* dishes before dinner.)
4. Zbog *prljave* vode nismo mogli da se kupamo u reci. (We couldn't swim in the river because of the *dirty* water.)
5. *Prljave* misli teško da ćeš moći da sakriješ od mene. (You can hardly hide your *dirty* thoughts from me.)
6. Naša komšinica ima naviku da baca smeće na *prljave* mesta. (Our neighbor has a habit of throwing garbage in *dirty* places.)
7. *Prljave* cipele ostavi napolju, molim te. (Please leave your *dirty* shoes outside.)
8. Soba je bila tako *prljava* da smo morali da unajmimo čistačicu. (The room was so *dirty* that we had to hire a cleaning lady.)

Note: The word "prljave" is used as an adjective in all of these examples and is declined to agree in gender and number with the noun it modifies. The translations are provided in parentheses.